ts]]\n| [[Sports game|Sports (association football)]]\n| 3\n| #1\n|-\n| ''[[Super Street Fighter II]]''\n| [[Capcom]]\n| [[Fighting game|Fighting]]\n| 3\n| #1\n|-\n| ''[[Breath of Fire (video game)|Breath of Fire]]''\n| [[Capcom]]\n| [[Role-playing video game|Role-playing]]\n| 3\n| #2\n|}\n\n;Highest-selling [[Sega Genesis]] titles of 1994\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! Title !! Publisher !! Genre(s) !! # of charting months !! Peak position\n|-\n| ''[[NHL '94]]''\n| [[EA Sports]]\n| [[Sports game|Sports (ice hockey)]]\n| 8\n| #4\n|-\n| ''[[FIFA International Soccer]]''\n| [[EA Sports]]\n| [[Sports game|Sports (association football)]]\n| 7\n| #3\n|-\n| ''[[World Series Baseball (video game)|World Series Baseball]]''\n| [[Sega]]\n| [[Sports game|Sports (baseball)]]\n| 6\n| #1\n|-\n| ''[[Ms. Pac-Man]]''\n| [[Tengen (company)|Tengen]]\n| [[List of maze video games|Maze]]\n| 6\n| #3\n|-\n| ''[[NBA Jam (1993 video game)|NBA Jam]]''\n| [[Acclaim Entertainment]]\n| [[Sports game|Sports (basketball)]]\n| 5\n| #1\n|-\n| ''[[NBA Showdown (video game)|NBA Showdown]]''\n| [[EA Sports]]\n| [[Sports game|Sports (basketball)]]\n| 5\n| #3\n|-\n| ''[[Mortal Kombat II]]''\n| [[Acclaim Entertainment]]\n| [[Fighting game|Fighting]]\n| 4\n| #1\n|-\n| ''[[Bill Walsh College Football '95]]''\n| [[EA Sports]]\n| [[Sports game|Sports (American football)]]\n| 4\n| #2\n|-\n| ''[[Madden NFL '94]]''\n| [[EA Sports]]\n| [[Sports game|Sports (American football)]]\n| 4\n| #3\n|-\n| ''[[PGA Tour Golf II]]''\n| [[EA Sports]]\n| [[Sports game|Sports (golf)]]\n| 4\n| #8\n|}\n\n;Highest-selling [[Sega CD]] titles of 1994\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! Title !! Publisher !! Genre(s) !! # of charting months !! Peak position\n|-\n| ''[[Tomcat Alley]]''\n| [[Sega]]\n| [[Interactive movie]]\n| 7\n| #1\n|-\n| ''[[Dragon's Lair (1983 video game)|Dragon's Lair]]''\n| [[ReadySoft Incorporated]]\n| [[Interactive movie]]\n| 7\n| #1\n|-\n| ''[[Star Wars: Rebel Assault]]''\n| [[LucasArts]]\n| [[Rail shooter]]\n| 6\n| #1\n|-\n| ''[[Ground Zero: Texas]]''\n| [[Sony Imagesoft]]\n| [[Interactive movie]]\n| 6\n| #1\n|-\n| ''[[Lunar: The Silver Star]]''\n| [[Game Arts]]\n| [[Role-playing video game|Role-playing]]\n| 6\n| #2\n|-\n| ''[[Rise of the Dragon]]''\n| [[Sierra Entertainment]]\n| [[Graphic adventure game|Graphic adventure]]\n| 6\n| #4\n|-\n| ''[[Lethal Enforcers]]''\n| [[Konami]]\n| [[Shooter game|Shooter]]\n| 5\n| #4\n|-\n| ''[[Vay (video game)|Vay]]''\n| [[SIMS Co., Ltd.]]\n| [[Role-playing video game|Role-playing]]\n| 4\n| #2\n|-\n| ''[[Dark Wizard]]''\n| [[Sega]]\n| [[Role-playing video game|Role-playing]]\n| 4\n| #2\n|-\n| ''[[The Third World War (video game)|The Third World War]]''\n| [[Micronet co., Ltd.]]\n| [[Strategy video game|Strategy]]\n| 4\n| #3\n|}\n\n;Highest-selling [[Game Gear]] titles of 1994\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! Title !! Publisher !! Genre(s) !! # of charting months !! Peak position\n|-\n| ''[[NBA Jam (1993 video game)|NBA Jam]]''\n| [[Acclaim Entertainment]]\n| [[Sports game|Sports (basketball)]]\n| 9\n| #1\n|-\n| ''[[X-Men (Game Gear video game)|X-Men]]''\n| [[Sega]]\n| [[Action game|Action]]\n| 9\n| #1\n|-\n| ''[[Sonic Chaos]]''\n| [[Sega]]\n| [[Platform game|Platform]]\n| 9\n| #1\n|-\n| ''[[Disney's Aladdin (1994 video game)|Disney's Aladdin]]''\n| [[Sega]]\n| [[Action game|Action]]\n| 8\n| #1\n|-\n| ''[[Mortal Kombat (1992 video game)|Mortal Kombat]]''\n| [[Acclaim Entertainment]]\n| [[Fighting game|Fighting]]\n| 8\n| #2\n|-\n| ''[[Ecco the Dolphin (video game)|Ecco the Dolphin]]''\n| [[Sega]]\n| [[Action-adventure game|Action-adventure]]\n| 8\n| #7\n|-\n| ''[[Road Rash (video game)|Road Rash]]''\n| [[U.S. Gold]]\n| [[Racing game|Racing]]\n| 6\n| #6\n|-\n| ''[[Winter Olympics (video game)|Winter Olympics]]''\n| [[U.S. Gold]]\n| [[Sports game|Sports (Olympics)]]\n| 5\n| #3\n|-\n| ''[[Poker Face Paul|Poker Face Paul's Solitare]]''\n| [[Sega]]